MPHO Makola is in no longer a Buccaneer! This is after the former Bafana Bafana midfielder reached an agreement with Orlando Pirates to part ways. The club has confirmed an agreement has been reached for the mutual termination of the contract, following a meeting between the parties. Makola joined the club seven years, going on to make well over 170 appearances for the Buccaneers. “The Club would like to thank Mr Makola for his service and wish him the best of luck in his future endeavours,” the club said. Armed with his clearance, Makola can join any team. But it is unclear at this stage whether he has any offers lined up 